Context: $ARGUMENTS

RULES (follow in order):
1. If stop_hook_active is true in the context, ALWAYS respond: {"decision": "approve", "reason": "Post-run already completed"}
2. Look at the conversation. If Claude just completed an automation run (creating courses on ATP Hub, browser automation using read_page/left_click/form_input on PMI ATP website), respond: {"decision": "block", "reason": "Automation run detected. Execute the /post-run command now to capture learnings before stopping."}
3. If this was NOT an automation run (just a question, file edit, health check, /apply-pending, or any non-automation task), respond: {"decision": "approve", "reason": "Not an automation run"}

Respond with JSON only. No other text.

